The '''masked tanager''' ('''''Stilpnia nigrocincta''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Thraupidae]]. It is found in [[Bolivia]], [[Brazil]], [[Colombia]], [[Ecuador]], [[Guyana]], [[Peru]], and [[Venezuela]]. Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s and heavily degraded former forest.

